OL,6,FThey also rejected the contention that
OL,7,Fthe operational structure of the ICRIR
OL,8,Flacked independence, noting that
OL,9,FGovernment involvement in the
OL,10,Fappointment of its commissioner or its
OL,11,Ffunding arrangements was "not unlawful
OL,12,For unusual".
OL,14,FBut the judges allowed the appeal on
OL,15,Fother grounds. This included ruling
OL,16,Fthat the commission is incompatible
OL,17,Fwith the European Convention on Human
OL,18,FRights (ECHR) in relation to the power
OL,19,Fheld by Northern Ireland Secretary
OL,20,FHilary Benn to withhold sensitive
OL,21,Fstate files from bereaved families.
